<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-21T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841.711/2812: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-21T17:00:00+00:00">November 21, 1939—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 21—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2416. A note based on your 1448, November 17, 7 p.m., has been sent
                                to the Foreign Office.<note n="61" xml:id="d228fn61">Copy of note
                                    No. 1563, November 20, 1939, was sent to the Department by the
                                    Ambassador as an enclosure to his despatch No. 4548, February 3,
                                    1940; neither printed.</note> I had previously taken up
                                personally with Lord Halifax the question of interference by naval
                                and censorship <pb facs="0277" n="269" xml:id="pg_269"/> authorities
                                with my personal mail, three instances of which have occurred, but I
                                have not yet received a reply from him.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>